---
// Article 1.5: RELA and Civil Defence (APM)
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/panduan-rakyat/Breadcrumb';

const articleData = {
  sectionNumber: '01',
  sectionTitle: 'Safety and Emergencies',
  sectionIcon: '🚨',
  articleTitle: 'RELA and Civil Defence (APM)',
  articleDescription: 'Volunteer organizations and civil defence services',
  colorRgb: '220, 38, 38',
  lastUpdated: 'March 2026',
};

const simpleContent = `
  <h2 id="who-are-they">Who are RELA and APM?</h2>
  <p>RELA and APM are groups of trained Malaysians who help during emergencies and disasters. They are not the police or the army, but they work alongside them to keep communities safe.</p>
  
  <h2 id="what-they-do">What do they do?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Help during floods, fires, and other disasters.</li>
    <li>Assist police during big events or emergencies.</li>
    <li>Run community safety programmes.</li>
    <li>Provide first aid training to the public.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="can-i-join">Can I join when I grow up?</h2>
  <p>Yes. When you are 18 years old, you can apply to join RELA or APM. You do not need to be a soldier or police officer. You just need to be a Malaysian citizen who wants to help your community.</p>

  <h2 id="how-to-contact">How do you contact them?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>RELA:</strong> rela.gov.my or 03-8883 3888</li>
    <li><strong>APM:</strong> apm.gov.my or 991</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="difference">What's the difference?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>RELA</strong> - Community volunteers who help with safety and public order</li>
    <li><strong>APM</strong> - Trained civil defence force for disaster response</li>
  </ul>
`;

const detailedContent = `
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>Malaysia has two key civilian support forces that operate alongside its uniformed emergency services. RELA (Ikatan Relawan Rakyat) functions as a grassroots civilian volunteer corps under KDN, focused on community safety, public order support, and disaster relief assistance. APM (Angkatan Pertahanan Awam Malaysia), or the Civil Defence Force, operates under the Ministry of Home Affairs with a specific mandate for civil protection, disaster preparedness, and emergency response coordination.</p>

  <h2 id="comparison">RELA vs APM at a Glance</h2>
  <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-border my-4">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-muted">
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">Feature</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">RELA</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">APM</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Full Name</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Ikatan Relawan Rakyat</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Angkatan Pertahanan Awam Malaysia</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Under</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Ministry of Home Affairs (KDN)</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Ministry of Home Affairs (KDN)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Nature</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Civilian volunteer corps</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Civil Defence Force</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Primary Role</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Community safety, public order support</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Disaster preparedness, civil protection</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Legal Powers</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Limited enforcement during deployment</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Civil Defence Act 1951 powers</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Minimum Age</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">18 years</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">18 years</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Website</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">rela.gov.my</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">apm.gov.my</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="rela-role">RELA's Role</h2>
  <h3>Primary Functions:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Community Patrol:</strong> Neighborhood safety patrols</li>
    <li><strong>Disaster Relief:</strong> Assist at relief centers during floods and disasters</li>
    <li><strong>Event Support:</strong> Crowd management at public events</li>
    <li><strong>Immigration Support:</strong> Assist with documentation checks</li>
    <li><strong>Traffic Control:</strong> Assist PDRM during peak hours or accidents</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>How to Join RELA:</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Visit your nearest KDN district office</li>
    <li>Bring MyKad and 2 passport-sized photos</li>
    <li>Fill out application form</li>
    <li>Undergo background check</li>
    <li>Complete basic training (2-4 weeks)</li>
    <li>Receive uniform and ID card</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="apm-role">APM's Role</h2>
  <h3>Primary Functions:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Search and Rescue:</strong> Urban search and rescue (USAR), water rescue</li>
    <li><strong>Disaster Response:</strong> First responder during earthquakes, landslides, floods</li>
    <li><strong>Public Education:</strong> Community disaster preparedness training</li>
    <li><strong>First Aid Training:</strong> Certified first aid and CPR courses</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Communications:</strong> Coordinate disaster communications</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>How to Join APM:</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Visit your state APM headquarters</li>
    <li>Bring MyKad, educational certificates, and photos</li>
    <li>Fill out application form</li>
    <li>Pass medical examination</li>
    <li>Complete basic training (3 months)</li>
    <li>Receive uniform, rank, and assignments</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="training">Training Programmes Available to Public</h2>
  <h3>APM Public Courses:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Basic First Aid:</strong> 2-day course (free or nominal fee)</li>
    <li><strong>CPR and AED:</strong> 1-day certification course</li>
    <li><strong>Disaster Preparedness:</strong> Community workshops</li>
    <li><strong>Fire Safety:</strong> Basic firefighting and prevention</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Contact your nearest APM state headquarters to register for courses.</p>

  <h2 id="real-scenarios">Real Scenarios</h2>
  <h3>Scenario 1: Flood Relief Center Management</h3>
  <p>During the 2022 Klang Valley floods, over 3,000 RELA volunteers were deployed to relief centers across Selangor to assist JKM with registration, food distribution, and basic crowd management. They do not conduct water rescues but play a critical role in keeping relief operations organised.</p>

  <h3>Scenario 2: APM Earthquake Response Training</h3>
  <p>Following the 2015 Ranau earthquake, APM conducted community disaster preparedness workshops across Sabah, teaching residents how to respond to earthquakes, build emergency kits, and perform basic search and rescue techniques.</p>

  <h3>Scenario 3: Big Event Support</h3>
  <p>During a major public event at Dataran Merdeka, RELA volunteers supported PDRM with crowd management, directing attendees and maintaining orderly access to exits. RELA members are frequently activated for national celebrations and large public gatherings.</p>

  <h2 id="important-numbers">Important Numbers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>999</strong> - General emergency</li>
    <li><strong>991</strong> - Civil Defence (APM emergency)</li>
    <li><strong>RELA Headquarters:</strong> 03-8883 3888</li>
    <li><strong>APM Headquarters:</strong> 03-8064 3000</li>
    <li><strong>RELA Website:</strong> rela.gov.my</li>
    <li><strong>APM Website:</strong> apm.gov.my</li>
  </ul>
`;

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Do I need to pay to join RELA or APM?",
    answer: "No, joining is free. However, you may need to pay for your own uniform items or optional advanced training courses. Basic training is provided free of charge."
  },
  {
    question: "Can women join RELA and APM?",
    answer: "Yes, both organizations welcome women. Many women serve in both RELA and APM, including in leadership positions and operational roles."
  },
  {
    question: "What is the time commitment?",
    answer: "RELA volunteers typically commit 8-16 hours per month for patrols and community service. APM members have more intensive commitments, especially during training periods and disaster responses."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I join if I have a full-time job?",
    answer: "Yes, many RELA and APM members have full-time jobs. Activities are often scheduled on weekends or evenings. However, you may need to take emergency leave during major disasters."
  },
  {
    question: "Do RELA and APM members get paid?",
    answer: "No, both are volunteer organizations. However, members may receive allowances during active disaster deployment or major event assignments. Some employers also provide special leave for volunteer duties."
  }
];

const headings = [
  { id: 'overview', title: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison', title: 'RELA vs APM Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'rela-role', title: "RELA's Role", level: 2 },
  { id: 'apm-role', title: "APM's Role", level: 2 },
  { id: 'training', title: 'Training Programmes', level: 2 },
  { id: 'real-scenarios', title: 'Real Scenarios', level: 2 },
];
---

<Layout title={`${articleData.articleTitle} | People's Guide | EduLaluan`}>
  <Header />

  <main class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section 
      class="relative overflow-hidden py-section-lg border-b"
      style={{
        '--section-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
        'border-bottom-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`
      }}
    >
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl">
          <!-- Breadcrumb -->
          <Breadcrumb items={[
            { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
            { label: "People's Guide", href: '/panduan-rakyat' },
            { label: `Section ${articleData.sectionNumber}`, href: `/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}` },
            { label: articleData.articleTitle }
          ]} />

          <!-- Back Button -->
          <a
            href={`/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}`}
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-primary transition-colors mb-6"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
            </svg>
            Back to Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}
          </a>

          <!-- Article Title -->
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mt-6">
            <div 
              class="flex h-16 w-16 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-3xl"
              style={{ 
                'backgroundColor': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
                'color': 'white'
              }}
            >
              {articleData.sectionIcon}
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary mb-1 tracking-wide uppercase">
                Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}: {articleData.sectionTitle}
              </p>
              <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-foreground">
                {articleData.articleTitle}
              </h1>
              <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mt-3">
                {articleData.articleDescription}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-surface">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="flex gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <!-- Main Content -->
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <!-- Audience Tabs (Simple/Detailed) -->
            <div class="mb-8">
              <!-- Tab Buttons -->
              <div class="mb-6 flex gap-2 rounded-xl bg-muted p-1.5">
                <button
                  id="tab-simple"
                  class="flex flex-1 items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold transition-all duration-200 bg-surface-elevated text-primary shadow-sm"
                  aria-pressed="true"
                  data-tab="simple"
                >
                  <span class="text-xl">🧒</span>
                  <span>Simple</span>
                </button>
                <button
                  id="tab-detailed"
                  class="flex flex-1 items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold transition-all duration-200 text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground"
                  aria-pressed="false"
                  data-tab="detailed"
                >
                  <span class="text-xl">🧑</span>
                  <span>Detailed</span>
                </button>
              </div>

              <!-- Tab Content -->
              <div id="content-simple" class="prose-panduan max-w-none tab-content" set:html={simpleContent} />
              <div id="content-detailed" class="prose-panduan max-w-none tab-content hidden" set:html={detailedContent} />
            </div>

            <script is:inline>
              document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
                const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('[data-tab]');
                const contents = {
                  simple: document.getElementById('content-simple'),
                  detailed: document.getElementById('content-detailed')
                };

                tabs.forEach(function(tab) {
                  tab.addEventListener('click', function() {
                    const selectedTab = this.getAttribute('data-tab');
                    
                    tabs.forEach(function(t) {
                      if (t.getAttribute('data-tab') === selectedTab) {
                        t.classList.add('bg-surface-elevated', 'text-primary', 'shadow-sm');
                        t.classList.remove('text-muted-foreground', 'hover:text-foreground');
                        t.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'true');
                      } else {
                        t.classList.remove('bg-surface-elevated', 'text-primary', 'shadow-sm');
                        t.classList.add('text-muted-foreground', 'hover:text-foreground');
                        t.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'false');
                      }
                    });

                    if (selectedTab === 'simple') {
                      contents.simple.classList.remove('hidden');
                      contents.detailed.classList.add('hidden');
                    } else {
                      contents.detailed.classList.remove('hidden');
                      contents.simple.classList.add('hidden');
                    }
                  });
                });
              });
            </script>

            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="mt-12">
              <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6">
                Frequently Asked Questions
              </h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                {faqs.map((faq) => (
                  <details
                    class="group rounded-xl border bg-surface-elevated transition-all"
                  >
                    <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 font-semibold text-foreground list-none">
                      {faq.question}
                      <svg
                        class="h-5 w-5 text-muted-foreground transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                      >
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                      </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-muted-foreground">
                      {faq.answer}
                    </div>
                  </details>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Last Updated -->
            <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-border">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                <strong>Last updated:</strong> {articleData.lastUpdated}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Table of Contents (Sidebar) -->
          <aside class="sticky top-24 hidden lg:block w-64 shrink-0">
            <nav class="space-y-1" aria-label="Table of contents">
              <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">
                On This Page
              </h3>
              {headings.map((heading) => (
                <a
                  href={`#${heading.id}`}
                  class="block py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
                  style={{ paddingLeft: `${(heading.level - 2) * 12 + 12}px` }}
                >
                  {heading.title}
                </a>
              ))}
            </nav>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation Footer -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-background">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-surface-elevated p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-muted-foreground">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p class="text-sm">
                <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only. Always verify with official sources for the most current information.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Section padding utilities */
  :root {
    --section-padding-lg: clamp(3rem, 5vw + 1rem, 5rem);
    --section-padding-md: clamp(2rem, 3vw + 1rem, 3rem);
  }

  .py-section-lg {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-lg);
  }

  .py-section-md {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-md);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-md);
  }

  /* Article Typography */
  .prose-panduan {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan ul,
  .prose-panduan ol {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan a {
    color: var(--primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .prose-panduan a:hover {
    color: var(--primary-dark);
  }

  .prose-panduan strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .prose-panduan th {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose-panduan td {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose-panduan .bg-muted {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
</style>
